The paper deals with the problem of sharing information among a group of agents, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The use of protocols and graphs of communication links suggests a focus on social networks and information theory, which are covered by cs.SI and cs.IT, respectively. Finally, the optimization of protocols and the study of variants with negative goals may involve machine learning techniques, which are part of the scope of cs.LG.
